[SN]TITLE[SN]
Hastings council leader Jeremy Birch dies in hospital

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The leader of Hastings Borough Council has died in hospital after what was thought to be a stroke.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Labour Councillor Jeremy Birch was taken to hospital after he fell ill on Friday afternoon and had remained in a medically-induced coma since then.
His partner issued a statement through Hastings council which said: "It is with great sadness that we announce the sudden death of Jeremy Birch."
She said the family wanted to thank the Conquest Hospital's critical care unit.
Mr Birch had been a member of the council since 1998 and the leader for a total of 13 years, over two separate periods.
Deputy leader Peter Chowney has taken over Mr Birch's duties.
